text.tspan: Inherent in a collection of data lies a story waiting to be found. Telling that story well requires knowing who
your audience is and knowing something about human perception.
The world is full of bad charts and graphs that discourage viewers from reading them. Many are filled with
clutter and put an unreasonable cognitive load on a viewer. Sometimes they even mislead by unethically
Anyone needing to communicate data should be aware of a few basic principles. This site addresses a few
of them and makes suggestions for moving beyond default Excel-generated charts. The default charts only
provide a starting basis. A good designer uses available tools to move beyond the defaults.
